# Cloudflare Pages rewrite rules.
#
# Vite copies everything in public/ to dist/ during build, so this file
# ends up at the root of the deployed site and Cloudflare Pages reads it.
#
# Rule 1: /api/* → Render backend, status 200 (rewrite, NOT redirect).
#         The browser keeps the original URL — same-origin from its
#         perspective — so no CORS preflight is needed.
# Rule 2: /* → /index.html, status 200. SPA fallback so any future
#         client-side routes resolve to the React app.

/api/*  https://tasklet-project.onrender.com/api/:splat  200
/*      /index.html                                       200
